FBIS4-14639 "drsov064_t_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-064 Daily Report 2 Apr 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Border With Russia Closed Border With Russia Closed LD0204212994 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 2055 GMT 2 Apr 94 LD0204212994 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] Estonia has closed the border with Russia and blocked roads in the vicinity after criminals attacked Russian border guards, killing one and wounding two. This was stated to RIA by Tomas Kyl, director-general of the Estonian Border Service Department. He said that the direction from which the attackers came has not yet been fully established. The chief of the Estonian border service also said that the criminals' appearances are already known and have been circulated along the entire border with Estonia, and border region residents have also been informed.
